display_errors (string): Determines whether errors should be printed directly on screen or hidden from user\
\
display_startup_errors (boolean): The display of errors which occur during PHP's startup sequence are handled separately from display_errors. PHP's default behavior is to suppress those errors from clients. Turning the display of startup errors on can be useful in debugging configuration problems. But, it's strongly recommended that you leave this setting off on production servers.\
\
log_errors (boolean): Logs all errors encountered on system into php_error_log file\
